00:29.279 --> 00:31.572
MAN:
Hey, howdy there, Mr. Lee.

00:31.740 --> 00:34.033
What is this? Filipino New Year's?

00:34.576 --> 00:36.035
No. Why you say that?

00:36.202 --> 00:37.870
Because you're cooking up a feast.

00:38.288 --> 00:40.664
I can smell it all the way
from the interstate.

00:40.832 --> 00:43.292
What is that? Barbecue?

00:43.460 --> 00:46.253
Oh, yeah. But it not coming from here.

00:46.796 --> 00:48.422
What is that noise?

00:50.341 --> 00:52.092
[RUMBLING]

00:54.179 --> 00:55.971
CHILD 1:
Daddy!

01:00.977 --> 01:03.187
- Daddy!
CHILD 2: Daddy!

01:03.354 --> 01:05.355
[MOOING]

01:18.453 --> 01:21.246
[FLYING SAUCER WHIRRING]

04:19.926 --> 04:22.803
What is your take on this, Jerry?

04:22.971 --> 04:25.681
The people are gonna love it,
Mr. President.

04:25.848 --> 04:30.394
Our only conflict is whether we ambush
the 6:00 news or hold out for prime time.

04:30.561 --> 04:32.938
Screw the press.
This is a need-to-know situation.

04:33.106 --> 04:34.648
We should make it top secret...

04:34.816 --> 04:36.984
...and move in right away
with DEFCON 4.

04:37.151 --> 04:39.111
Mr. President, we cannot sit on this.

04:40.989 --> 04:44.366
General Casey, do you have an opinion?

04:44.534 --> 04:47.286
Well, sir, do we know they're hostile?

04:47.453 --> 04:49.871
What do you mean,
"do we know they're hostile?"

04:50.039 --> 04:52.749
They have our planet surrounded
with thousands of warships.

04:52.917 --> 04:54.459
Do we know they're warships?

04:57.171 --> 04:58.213
[SIGHS]

04:58.381 --> 05:01.133
Professor, what do we know about them?

05:02.677 --> 05:05.095
We know they're extremely advanced
technologically...

05:05.263 --> 05:08.307
...which suggests, very rightfully so,
that they're peaceful.

05:09.183 --> 05:13.228
An advanced civilization is,
by definition, not barbaric.

05:13.396 --> 05:16.523
Mr. President, this is a great day.

05:17.066 --> 05:20.485
I and all my colleagues
are extremely excited.

05:21.404 --> 05:23.030
Good.

05:23.573 --> 05:26.408
Extraterrestrial life.

05:27.076 --> 05:28.577
You're right, Jerry.

05:28.745 --> 05:31.079
The people are gonna love it.

05:31.247 --> 05:33.707
This is a momentous occasion.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.380
- Mr. President, we have to act...
PRESIDENT: We'll go all media on this.

05:37.879 --> 05:42.215
I'll wear my blue Cerruti suit.
And, Jerry, I'll need a good speech.

05:42.383 --> 05:43.467
Statesman-like...

05:44.052 --> 05:47.929
...historical and yet warm and neighborly.

05:48.097 --> 05:51.892
Abraham Lincoln meets Leave It to Beaver.
You know the sort of thing. Heh.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.185
Yes, sir.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.103
WOMAN: Are they too old-fashioned?
MAN: Yes.

05:55.271 --> 05:56.730
WOMAN:
No, I don't think so.

05:56.898 --> 06:00.359
This has got the colors, but no.
I don't think so.

06:00.526 --> 06:02.069
- Not vivid enough.
MAN: Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

06:02.236 --> 06:04.863
- Nancy had this in the library, didn't she?
- Yes, indeed.

06:05.031 --> 06:06.156
I don't think so.

06:06.324 --> 06:09.951
I thought perhaps the watered silk.
And this week it's on sale.

06:10.119 --> 06:12.746
I hardly think I need worry about that.

06:12.914 --> 06:15.582
My husband is the leader
of the free world.

06:16.793 --> 06:18.877
What do you think, Taffy?

06:19.045 --> 06:22.631
Why don't you leave the Roosevelt Room
the way the Roosevelts wanted it?

06:22.799 --> 06:23.799
[LAUGHS]

06:23.966 --> 06:27.969
Because Eleanor Roosevelt
was too fond of chintz. That's why.

06:28.304 --> 06:30.430
Mother, this isn't your house.

06:30.598 --> 06:33.683
Taffy, if you're going to be a pest,
I'm going to ignore you.

06:34.227 --> 06:36.603
- Mrs. Dale?
- Yes?

06:42.485 --> 06:44.111
[HORNS HONK]

06:55.706 --> 06:57.332
[LAUGHING]

06:57.500 --> 07:01.420
- I saw you fight Sonny Liston in '69.
- Really?

07:01.587 --> 07:03.839
- You mean, you were a nun back then?
- Oh, yes.

07:04.006 --> 07:07.050
We've always been fight fans,
haven't we, sisters?

07:07.218 --> 07:09.094
WOMAN [OVER PA]:
Byron Williams, telephone.

07:09.262 --> 07:11.221
- Byron Williams....
- That's me. I gotta go.

07:11.389 --> 07:13.932
You ladies have a nice time, all right?
Thank you.

07:14.100 --> 07:15.851
[LAUGHING]

07:18.062 --> 07:19.396
- Yeah?
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]: Byron?

07:19.564 --> 07:20.605
Oh, Louise.

07:21.065 --> 07:23.150
LOUISE:
I'm sorry I have to call you at work.

07:23.901 --> 07:27.946
The boys haven't been home in two nights
and I don't know what to do.

07:28.406 --> 07:30.198
Listen, you're doing the best you can.

07:30.408 --> 07:32.159
They're just at that age.

07:34.203 --> 07:37.289
Louise, the casino manager's
giving me the evil eye. I've gotta go.

07:37.957 --> 07:39.666
I'll call you later, okay?

07:40.626 --> 07:43.628
Hey, are you still cool on me
coming to Washington?

07:43.796 --> 07:45.464
Sure. Of course I am.

07:46.174 --> 07:49.217
You take care, okay? Bye.

08:02.815 --> 08:04.107
Ahh....

08:04.442 --> 08:06.234
Do you have to drink in front of me?

08:06.402 --> 08:08.528
You're an adult. Just cope.

08:08.696 --> 08:11.823
It doesn't help me
that all we ever do is sit around in bars.

08:11.991 --> 08:14.117
Hey. This is work, baby, okay?

08:14.285 --> 08:17.704
I'm checking the decor,
the lighting, the traffic flow.

08:17.872 --> 08:21.082
If I'd known you'd turn into a crook,
I never would have married you.

08:21.250 --> 08:22.792
I'm not a crook.

08:22.960 --> 08:25.337
I'm ambitious. There's a difference.

08:25.505 --> 08:28.089
And if you think you can make
a nickel in this town...

08:28.257 --> 08:32.135
...without knowing how to dally
around a few curves, well...

08:32.303 --> 08:34.929
...you don't know doodlysquat
about the gaming industry.

08:35.097 --> 08:36.306
Oh, Art.

08:36.474 --> 08:40.434
Galaxy's gonna be
the best hotel in Vegas.

08:40.602 --> 08:43.020
The best. I promise.

08:43.188 --> 08:45.982
Don't you realize what you're doing?
Destroying the Earth.

08:46.150 --> 08:49.027
All this greed. This money system.

08:49.195 --> 08:50.904
You're destroying everything.

08:51.072 --> 08:53.990
Okay, okay, Barbara. Okay.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.826
Keep your voice down.

08:57.370 --> 08:59.663
I got friends here.

09:00.790 --> 09:03.250
Sugar. Hit me one more time.

09:03.417 --> 09:06.211
- Stop flirting with the waitress.
- Oh, God. Here.

09:07.964 --> 09:09.589
Go on over to the roulette...

09:11.259 --> 09:12.801
...play our anniversary...

09:12.969 --> 09:15.095
...and stay off of black.

09:18.307 --> 09:19.391
Thanks, honey.

09:20.935 --> 09:22.936
[HORN BLOWING]

09:24.564 --> 09:26.064
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

09:26.232 --> 09:27.482
Yeah?

09:27.650 --> 09:30.652
Make it quick.
We go out live in 10 minutes.

09:31.279 --> 09:34.823
What? The actual president?
What do you mean, "cutting in"?

09:35.908 --> 09:37.909
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

09:39.120 --> 09:41.997
Budget negotiations may be dead
in the water after this week.

09:42.748 --> 09:44.666
Hair looks good.

09:45.334 --> 09:46.376
I like the hair.

09:46.544 --> 09:48.438
...quote, "factually challenged."
Griffin says....

09:48.462 --> 09:49.504
[PHONE RINGS]

09:49.672 --> 09:51.339
Yeah, Stone. Speak.

09:51.507 --> 09:52.966
Jason, hi, it's me.

09:54.260 --> 09:55.927
You wearing a bra?

09:56.095 --> 09:59.764
Listen, this is big. President Dale
is cutting into my show today.

10:01.350 --> 10:04.352
That's absurd. Why would he stoop
to being on Today in Fashion?

10:04.520 --> 10:05.854
He's interrupting everybody.

10:06.022 --> 10:09.399
I don't know, it's some sort of
emergency announcement or something.

10:09.567 --> 10:11.985
This doesn't make sense.
He should be talking to us.

10:12.153 --> 10:13.236
[SCOFFS]

10:13.529 --> 10:15.822
White House is coming out live.

10:16.449 --> 10:19.159
Good evening, my fellow Americans.

10:19.785 --> 10:23.038
I apologize for interrupting
your regular programs...

10:23.205 --> 10:26.333
...but I have a very important
announcement to make.

10:27.043 --> 10:29.878
Many important things have happened
to me in my life:

10:30.671 --> 10:32.672
My graduation from Princeton...

10:33.633 --> 10:36.509
...the day that Marsha said
she would be my wife...

10:36.677 --> 10:38.762
...the birth of our daughter, Taffy.

10:38.929 --> 10:39.971
Thanks, Dad.

10:40.556 --> 10:42.724
And the news that I have heard today...

10:42.892 --> 10:45.018
- ...ranks right up there.
- Thank you.

10:45.770 --> 10:48.104
A powerful memory is in the making.

10:48.272 --> 10:49.898
Not just for me...

10:50.066 --> 10:52.067
...but for all mankind.

10:52.234 --> 10:57.947
Today, an extraordinary discovery
was made by the Hubble telescope.

10:58.991 --> 11:02.702
The data from the Hubble was decoded...

11:02.870 --> 11:05.030
...then analyzed
by the most powerful computers at MIT.

11:05.081 --> 11:07.916
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

11:08.084 --> 11:10.293
The images are undeniable.

11:10.961 --> 11:14.297
We are entering the dawn of a new era.

11:15.257 --> 11:18.927
Frame enlargements
provide an astonishing sight.

11:19.595 --> 11:24.099
A fleet of vehicles,
which can best be described as...

11:24.266 --> 11:25.642
...flying saucers.

11:25.810 --> 11:29.479
Come on. Come on.
Papa needs a new pair of shoes.

11:29.647 --> 11:31.523
Hey!

11:32.108 --> 11:34.150
Hey, am I the only one
shooting craps here?

11:34.318 --> 11:37.737
PRESIDENT:... we will have
the opportunity to meet with them.

11:37.905 --> 11:41.074
I feel this is the perfect summation
to the 20th century....

11:41.242 --> 11:43.284
Martians.

11:43.452 --> 11:44.911
This is great.

11:46.163 --> 11:48.665
Please come to Earth. Please.

11:49.291 --> 11:50.583
We need you.

11:50.918 --> 11:52.919
[PRESIDENT TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

11:54.964 --> 11:57.132
ART:
I got people coming in.

11:57.299 --> 12:00.301
Everybody wants to be a part of this.

12:00.469 --> 12:03.346
Galaxy's gonna be world-class.

12:03.806 --> 12:05.140
And soon...

12:05.307 --> 12:08.351
...we will become one solar system.

12:08.894 --> 12:10.687
What the hell is he talking about?

12:10.855 --> 12:14.315
These flying saucers
have come from the planet Mars...

12:14.483 --> 12:17.694
- ...and at their current course and speed....
- Oh. Hey.

12:17.862 --> 12:23.450
Listen, Hoss. I've been thinking about
Martians when there wasn't no Martians.

12:23.743 --> 12:28.329
It is profoundly moving
to know there is intelligent life out there.

12:28.497 --> 12:29.789
Glad they got it somewhere.

12:29.957 --> 12:34.335
And our world will never feel
quite the same again.

12:35.546 --> 12:37.297
Good night...

12:37.840 --> 12:39.841
...and God bless you all.

12:50.102 --> 12:51.936
This...

12:52.313 --> 12:53.521
...is intense.

12:53.689 --> 12:55.064
[PHONE RINGS]

12:55.357 --> 12:56.441
[BARKING]

12:56.817 --> 12:58.693
Shut up, Poppy. Shut up.

12:59.695 --> 13:01.529
Shut up.

13:01.864 --> 13:03.698
Jason Stone.

13:06.035 --> 13:07.702
It's for you.

13:08.871 --> 13:11.414
Poppy, honey. No, sweetie.

13:13.459 --> 13:17.212
That's right. Shh. Good girl. Yeah?

13:18.130 --> 13:21.508
Yeah. Well, I could be there at...

13:21.675 --> 13:23.468
...I don't know, 11.

13:24.428 --> 13:26.596
Okay, bye-bye.

13:29.058 --> 13:30.517
[SIGHS]

13:36.565 --> 13:38.066
Yes?

13:38.943 --> 13:42.153
Oh, they want me to go interview
that professor from the White House.

13:43.155 --> 13:44.906
Kessler?

13:45.950 --> 13:48.243
- Donald Kessler?
- Yeah, I think that was his name.

13:48.410 --> 13:51.079
You know, the science guy.

13:51.247 --> 13:53.456
This is nuts, this is....

13:53.624 --> 13:55.124
We should have got that guy.

13:56.085 --> 13:59.045
Well, I can't help it
if your people are too slow.

13:59.213 --> 14:00.255
Right, Poppy?

14:00.422 --> 14:02.757
[BARKING]

14:14.103 --> 14:16.104
[MAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER TV]

14:24.280 --> 14:27.282
- Finished!
- One minute, 57 seconds.

14:27.616 --> 14:30.952
- Ha-ha! Didn't I tell you under two minutes?
- You did.

14:31.120 --> 14:33.872
You did. I'm so proud of you.

14:34.039 --> 14:36.708
- Hey, Ma, you want a doughnut?
- How old are they?

14:36.876 --> 14:38.001
Fresh-baked Monday.

14:38.586 --> 14:41.462
Richie, that's six days ago.

14:41.630 --> 14:42.922
Okay, give me a couple.

14:46.635 --> 14:49.095
Hey, this Martian thing
is pretty awesome, huh?

14:49.263 --> 14:52.974
Did any one of you traitors
see my Muffy?

14:53.142 --> 14:54.851
Your brother's gonna volunteer.

14:55.019 --> 14:57.145
BILLY GLENN:
As soon as I get back to the base.

14:57.313 --> 15:00.106
- Volunteer for what, Billy Glenn?
- Martian detail.

15:00.274 --> 15:01.941
- Uh-huh.
- Cool.

15:02.109 --> 15:04.110
If any of them Martians
come around here...

15:04.278 --> 15:06.404
...I'm gonna kick their butts.
Heh-heh-heh.

15:15.873 --> 15:17.916
[ELECTRONIC GUNSHOTS]

15:18.125 --> 15:19.667
Jump!

15:28.719 --> 15:31.054
Excuse me, folks,
but we gotta make an unscheduled stop.

15:31.221 --> 15:32.513
[TIRES SCREECH]

15:34.516 --> 15:36.351
It's Mama.

15:36.518 --> 15:39.687
What are you doing here? Huh?
If you ain't home, why ain't you in class?

15:39.855 --> 15:42.398
- Mama, class was canceled.
- Class was not canceled.

15:42.566 --> 15:44.150
- Come here. Come here.
- For what?

15:44.318 --> 15:46.069
I'm not gonna hurt you.
Now, come here.

15:46.236 --> 15:48.029
Let go of him.

15:48.697 --> 15:51.074
Okay. Now, just come here.

15:51.659 --> 15:53.409
Come here.

15:54.078 --> 15:55.536
Think it's smart to cut school?

15:55.704 --> 15:58.206
- What are you doing?
- Do you? Do you? Huh? Huh?

15:58.374 --> 15:59.666
- No.
- "No, Mama." It's dumb.

15:59.833 --> 16:01.834
- You're gonna flunk and go to jail.
CEDRIC: No.

16:02.002 --> 16:05.421
Get your butt on the bus.
Get on that bus, boy.

16:05.589 --> 16:07.715
I'll be tripping all over you.
Get back there.

16:07.883 --> 16:10.551
- I don't want to hear another word.
CEDRIC: I hate school.

16:10.719 --> 16:12.637
I heard that.

16:35.369 --> 16:36.911
WOMAN 1: Hi.
- Hi there.

16:37.079 --> 16:40.039
WOMAN 1: Want a date?
WOMAN 2: How about it?

16:40.207 --> 16:41.833
A date?

16:43.794 --> 16:44.836
Sounds good.

16:45.004 --> 16:47.171
[ALL CHUCKLING]

16:47.464 --> 16:49.007
The stress at work is...

16:49.508 --> 16:51.551
...unbelievable.

16:56.432 --> 16:58.266
Mr. Bava, can I speak to you in private?

16:58.434 --> 17:01.394
No, I gotta watch the floor.
What do you want, Byron?

17:01.562 --> 17:05.022
- I'm supporting my family back East.
- I thought you were divorced.

17:05.607 --> 17:08.943
Well, I am,
but I still have to take care of them.

17:09.111 --> 17:11.988
Anyway, look. Things have been
a little lean around here...

17:12.156 --> 17:14.365
...and I was wondering
if I could get a raise?

17:14.532 --> 17:17.452
- Out of the question.
- Mr. Bava, I'm an asset to this hotel.

17:17.618 --> 17:20.579
- I mean, they like me around here.
- Byron, you're a nice guy.

17:21.165 --> 17:24.709
But I can get Leon Spinks or Buster Douglas
for the same money, maybe less.

17:25.252 --> 17:28.421
You better get moving.
You're on in five minutes.

17:31.800 --> 17:33.801
[WHIRRING]

17:36.597 --> 17:37.638
[CHUCKLES]

17:37.806 --> 17:40.391
This show's gonna get
a hell of a rating.

17:40.601 --> 17:41.684
It's all yours, Ian.

17:41.852 --> 17:44.771
...language you choose to employ,
and in certain circumstances...

17:44.938 --> 17:47.648
...the proposition that two and two
equals five...

17:47.816 --> 17:49.650
...is entirely legitimate.

17:51.570 --> 17:52.612
Call me Nathalie.

17:53.322 --> 17:55.990
And you, do please call me Donald.

17:57.493 --> 17:59.577
I've always admired your show.

18:01.455 --> 18:03.873
Really? You like my work?

18:04.541 --> 18:06.167
Yes. Very much.

18:06.335 --> 18:08.086
Why....

18:08.337 --> 18:10.046
Why, thank you.

18:10.214 --> 18:11.881
MAN:
Coming out of commercial.

18:12.049 --> 18:15.968
In five, four, three, two....

18:16.136 --> 18:21.015
Welcome back. We're speaking
with Professor Donald Kessler.

18:21.183 --> 18:27.396
He's the chairman
of the American Academy of Astronautics.

18:28.107 --> 18:29.440
Professor...

18:29.608 --> 18:32.985
...isn't it weird that we sent
a space probe to Mars...

18:33.153 --> 18:34.737
...and we didn't even find anyone?

18:35.572 --> 18:38.282
Well, not really, Nathalie...

18:39.451 --> 18:41.536
...because we didn't get into the canals.

18:41.703 --> 18:43.579
The Martian canals are actually canyons.

18:44.039 --> 18:46.040
Some of them are over 100 miles deep.

18:46.500 --> 18:48.876
The Martian civilization
has clearly developed...

18:49.044 --> 18:51.420
...under the surface of the planet.

18:51.588 --> 18:54.757
Their science and technology
must be absolutely mind-boggling.

18:56.093 --> 19:00.471
So, what, in your view, Donald Kessler...

19:00.639 --> 19:04.892
...chairman, are some of the things
that the Martians can teach us, professor?

19:07.563 --> 19:10.022
KESSLER:
Quite a lot about Mars, I expect, Nathalie.

19:10.190 --> 19:11.691
[GIGGLES]

19:11.859 --> 19:12.984
[CHUCKLES]

19:13.652 --> 19:14.735
She's flirting with him.

19:14.945 --> 19:18.489
Ahem. But seriously,
this is tremendously exciting.

19:18.657 --> 19:21.784
Think of it. The knowledge, new ideas.
It's gonna change everything.

19:22.411 --> 19:24.162
And we must be open to it.

19:24.329 --> 19:26.873
Maybe they can tell us
about our universe.

19:27.040 --> 19:29.208
How it started. Where it's going.

19:29.376 --> 19:32.378
Perhaps even its purpose.

19:33.422 --> 19:34.755
It's tremendously exciting.

19:34.923 --> 19:40.469
This is the most important thing to happen
since Jesus walked in Galilee.

19:40.637 --> 19:43.806
Oh, Christ. What's wrong with the picture?

19:43.974 --> 19:45.141
Go to Camera 2!

19:45.309 --> 19:46.642
I can't. It's busted.

19:46.810 --> 19:48.561
Well, then go to 1. Go to 4.

19:48.729 --> 19:51.314
[STATIC HUMMING]

19:52.024 --> 19:53.608
[POPPY WHIMPERS]

19:55.277 --> 19:56.319
He just copped a feel.

19:59.281 --> 20:00.364
Now what?

20:02.451 --> 20:03.743
[POPPY BARKING]

20:13.545 --> 20:14.587
What's that?

20:15.547 --> 20:16.797
So that's a Martian.

20:20.260 --> 20:21.427
That's a Martian?

20:22.512 --> 20:23.804
[BARKS]

20:23.972 --> 20:25.092
[SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

20:25.265 --> 20:27.642
- Oh, my God.
- Yikes.

20:30.562 --> 20:32.521
I'm not gonna have that thing
in my house.

20:33.357 --> 20:34.398
[CHUCKLES]

20:34.566 --> 20:38.611
Sweetie, we may have to. The people
will expect me to meet with them.

20:38.779 --> 20:41.197
Well, they're not gonna eat off
the Van Buren china.

20:41.365 --> 20:42.740
[SPEAKING IN ALIEN LANGUAGE]

20:42.908 --> 20:45.326
Oh, look at that brain.

20:45.494 --> 20:46.953
He must be real smart.

20:47.621 --> 20:49.580
It's gross.

20:49.998 --> 20:51.666
